quran[12]{c,v,t,f}:
  11,103,"Indeed in that is a sign for those who fear the punishment of the Hereafter. That is a Day for which the people will be collected, and that is a Day [which will be] witnessed."
  11,104,"And We do not delay it except for a limited term."
  11,105,"The Day it comes no soul will speak except by His permission. And among them will be the wretched and the prosperous."
  12,64,"He said, "
  12,65,"And when they opened their baggage, they found their merchandise returned to them. They said, ",footnotes:1:For them.  Or one obtained by us with ease.
  12,66,"[Jacob] said, ",footnotes:1:i.e., sufficient to witness and deal with the matter.
  13,31,"And if there was any Qur’ān [i.e., recitation] by which the mountains would be removed or the earth would be broken apart or the dead would be made to speak,{1} [it would be this Qur’ān], but to Allāh belongs the affair entirely. Then have those who believed not accepted that had Allāh willed, He would have guided the people, all of them? And those who disbelieve do not cease to be struck, for what they have done, by calamity - or it will descend near their home - until there comes the promise of Allāh. Indeed, Allāh does not fail in [His] promise.",footnotes:1:As suggested by the disbelievers.
  13,32,"And already were [other] messengers ridiculed before you, and I extended the time of those who disbelieved; then I seized them, and how [terrible] was My penalty."
  13,33,"Then is He who is a maintainer of every soul, [knowing] what it has earned, [like any other]? But to Allāh they have attributed partners. Say, ",footnotes:1:[i.e., other "deities."],footnotes:2:[i.e., your attributing of divinity to other than Allāh.]
  14,10,"Their messengers said, "
  14,11,"Their messengers said to them, "
  14,12,"And why should we not rely upon Allāh while He has guided us to our [good] ways. And we will surely be patient against whatever harm you should cause us. And upon Allāh let those who would rely [indeed] rely."
